    "surah_info": {
        "surah_name": "Surah Al-Infitar",
        "ayah_count": "19",
        "revelation_place": "Mecca",
        "description": "Name\nIt is derived from the word infatarat in the first verse. Infitar is an infinitive which means to cleave or split asunder, thereby implying that it is the Surah in which the splitting asunder of the sky has been mentioned.\nPeriod of Revelation\nThis Surah and the Surah At-Takwir closely resemble each other in their subject matter. This shows that both were sent down in about the same period.\nTheme and Subject Matter\nIts theme is the Hereafter. According to a tradition related in Musnad Ahmad, Tirmidhi, Ibn al-Mundhir, Tabarani, Hakim and Ibn Marduyah, on the authority of Hadrat Abdullah bin Umar, the Holy Messenger (upon whom be peace) said: \"The one who wants that he should see the Resurrection Day as one would see it with one's eyes, should read Surah At-Takwir, Surah Al-Infitar and Surah Al-Inshiqaq.\"\nIn this Surah first the Resurrection Day has been described and it is said that when it occurs, every person will see whatever he has done in the world. After this, man has been asked to ponder the question: \"O man, what has deluded you into thinking that the God, Who brought you into being and by Whose favor and bounty you possess the finest body, limbs and features among all creatures, is only bountiful and not just? His being bountiful and generous does not mean that you should become fearless of His justice.\"Then, man has been warned, so as to say: \"Do not remain involved in any misunderstanding. Your complete record is being prepared. There are trustworthy writers who are writing down whatever you do.\" In conclusion, it has been forcefully stated that the Day of Resurrection will surely take place when the righteous shall enjoy every kind of bliss in Paradise and the wicked shall be punished in Hell. On that day no one shall avail anyone anything. All powers of judgment\r\nshall be with Allah."
    },
    "surah_verses": [
        {
            "verse_key": "82:1",
            "verse_num": "82:1",
            "arabic_text": " إِذَا ٱلسَّمَآءُ ٱنفَطَرَتْ",
            "en_text": "When the sky splits open,"
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "82:2",
            "verse_num": "82:2",
            "arabic_text": "وَإِذَا ٱلْكَوَاكِبُ ٱنتَثَرَتْ",
            "en_text": "and when the stars fall away,"
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "82:3",
            "verse_num": "82:3",
            "arabic_text": "وَإِذَا ٱلْبِحَارُ فُجِّرَتْ",
            "en_text": "and when the seas burst forth,"
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "82:4",
            "verse_num": "82:4",
            "arabic_text": "وَإِذَا ٱلْقُبُورُ بُعْثِرَتْ",
            "en_text": "and when the graves spill out,"
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "82:5",
            "verse_num": "82:5",
            "arabic_text": "عَلِمَتْ نَفْسٌ مَّا قَدَّمَتْ وَأَخَّرَتْ",
            "en_text": "˹then˺ each soul will know what it has sent forth or left behind."
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "82:6",
            "verse_num": "82:6",
            "arabic_text": "يَـٰٓأَيُّهَا ٱلْإِنسَـٰنُ مَا غَرَّكَ بِرَبِّكَ ٱلْكَرِيمِ",
            "en_text": "O humanity! What has emboldened you against your Lord, the Most Generous,"
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "82:7",
            "verse_num": "82:7",
            "arabic_text": "ٱلَّذِى خَلَقَكَ فَسَوَّىٰكَ فَعَدَلَكَ",
            "en_text": "Who created you, fashioned you, and perfected your design,"
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "82:8",
            "verse_num": "82:8",
            "arabic_text": "فِىٓ أَىِّ صُورَةٍ مَّا شَآءَ رَكَّبَكَ",
            "en_text": "moulding you in whatever form He willed?"
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "82:9",
            "verse_num": "82:9",
            "arabic_text": "كَلَّا بَلْ تُكَذِّبُونَ بِٱلدِّينِ",
            "en_text": "But no! In fact, you deny the ˹final˺ Judgment,"
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "82:10",
            "verse_num": "82:10",
            "arabic_text": "وَإِنَّ عَلَيْكُمْ لَحَـٰفِظِينَ",
            "en_text": "while you are certainly observed by vigilant,"
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "82:11",
            "verse_num": "82:11",
            "arabic_text": "كِرَامًا كَـٰتِبِينَ",
            "en_text": "honourable angels, recording ˹everything˺."
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "82:12",
            "verse_num": "82:12",
            "arabic_text": "يَعْلَمُونَ مَا تَفْعَلُونَ",
            "en_text": "They know whatever you do."
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "82:13",
            "verse_num": "82:13",
            "arabic_text": "إِنَّ ٱلْأَبْرَارَ لَفِى نَعِيمٍ",
            "en_text": "Indeed, the virtuous will be in bliss,"
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "82:14",
            "verse_num": "82:14",
            "arabic_text": "وَإِنَّ ٱلْفُجَّارَ لَفِى جَحِيمٍ",
            "en_text": "and the wicked will be in Hell,"
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "82:15",
            "verse_num": "82:15",
            "arabic_text": "يَصْلَوْنَهَا يَوْمَ ٱلدِّينِ",
            "en_text": "burning in it on Judgment Day,"
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "82:16",
            "verse_num": "82:16",
            "arabic_text": "وَمَا هُمْ عَنْهَا بِغَآئِبِينَ",
            "en_text": "and they will have no escape from it."
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "82:17",
            "verse_num": "82:17",
            "arabic_text": "وَمَآ أَدْرَىٰكَ مَا يَوْمُ ٱلدِّينِ",
            "en_text": "What will make you realize what Judgment Day is?"
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "82:18",
            "verse_num": "82:18",
            "arabic_text": "ثُمَّ مَآ أَدْرَىٰكَ مَا يَوْمُ ٱلدِّينِ",
            "en_text": "Again, what will make you realize what Judgment Day is?"
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "82:19",
            "verse_num": "82:19",
            "arabic_text": "يَوْمَ لَا تَمْلِكُ نَفْسٌ لِّنَفْسٍ شَيْـًٔا ۖ وَٱلْأَمْرُ يَوْمَئِذٍ لِّلَّهِ",
